Class LinkedList

java.lang.Object
  se.lypson.common.collections.LinkedList
Direct Known Subclasses:
Ring
public class LinkedList
extends java.lang.Object

A linked list class. This is functionally a subset of the LinkedList class available in Java SE, intented for use in Java ME.

Thread Safety:
Static methods are thread-safe. Instance methods are not guaranteed to be thread-safe.

Author:
Tobias Persson

iterator

public IListIterator iterator()

Returns an iterator for the list.

The returned iterator will have a position that is after the end of the list and before the beginning of the list - that is, if the IForwardIterator.next() method is called on the iterator before the IListIterator.previous() method is called on the iterator, the iterator is traversed from the beginning; otherwise, the list is traversed from the end.

Returns:
A IListIterator that traverses the list.
